ch.codebulb.lambdaomega

Class F<T,T1 extends T,T2 extends T,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.abstractions.OmegaObject
      • ch.codebulb.lambdaomega.F<T,T1,T2,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the function input type
    T1 - the type of the 1st function input if it takes two inputs; must be same as T otherwise
    T2 - the type of the 2nd function input if it takes two inputs; must be same as T otherwise
    R - the function return type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    I<T,R>, ReadonlyIndexedI<T,R>

    public class F<T,T1 extends T,T2 extends T,R>
extends OmegaObject
implements ReadonlyIndexedI<T,R>
    The "F" stands for "function". Provides a common interface for all FunctionalInterface implementations for which it acts as a wrapper.

    It also provides common static helper methods for functions.

    The constructor of this class is not visible; use the convenience f(Function) method to create a new instance of this class, or one of the other static helper constructor functions. It's best practice to statically import these functions in client code.

      • compare

        public static <T> Comparator<T> compare(Function<? super T,V2<Function<? super T,Comparable>,Boolean>>... keyExtractors)
        Returns a Comparator built from subsequently applying the keyExtractors provided. Every keyExtractor is a function f: (T) → V2<f1, Boolean> where the return type is a V2; its 1st element is the actual keyExtractor function f1, its 2nd element is a Boolean specifying the sort order for that specific keyExtractor: true for ascending.
